Programming 2 Machine Problem Set
CSV Dataset Processing using Java and JavaScript

Student Name: Gray Allen Arizala
Repository: uphsd-cs-arizala-grayallen

This project contains programs that process a CSV dataset using both Java and JavaScript. 
Each program asks the user to input the dataset file path before reading and processing the data. 
The programs use file reading methods to parse CSV rows and perform different data processing tasks.

------------------------------------------------------------

MP10 – Detect Duplicate Records

This program reads the CSV dataset and checks for duplicate rows. 
Each row is stored in a data structure that tracks unique records. 
If the program encounters a row that already exists, it is identified as a duplicate. 
The duplicate records are displayed along with the total number of duplicates found.

------------------------------------------------------------

MP11 – Frequency Count for Column Values

This program counts how many times values appear in a selected column of the dataset. 
The user enters the column index that will be analyzed. 
Each row is split into columns and the value from the chosen column is counted. 
The program then displays the frequency of each value found in that column.

------------------------------------------------------------

MP12 – Display Dataset in Formatted Table Output

This program reads the CSV dataset and prints the contents in a formatted table layout. 
Each row is separated into columns using the comma delimiter. 
The program formats the output so each column has equal spacing, making the dataset easier to read. 
This produces a structured table-like display in the console.




How to Run the Programs

Java:
1. Compile the program using: javac FileName.java
2. Run using: java FileName
3. Enter the dataset file path when prompted.

JavaScript:
1. Run using: node filename.js
2. Enter the dataset file path when prompted.